20.67. Suppose that G is a finite group, p is a prime, and B is a Brauer p-block of G with defect group D. Let cd(B) be the set of degrees of the irreducible complex characters in B.
a) Is it true that the derived length of D is bounded by |cd(B)|?
b) (A. Jaikin-Zapirain). Is is even true that |cd(D)| ⩽|cd(B)|?
G. Navarro
